keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>This paper outlines an approach to the development of a deductive object-oriented database system. The approach presented uses a formally defined object-oriented data model as the starting point for the development of a logic query language and an imperative database programming language. These languages can be used independently — the logic language for expressing queries or defining rule-based applications, the imperative language for manipulating the database — or together to support a flexible system for data-intensive application development.</abstract></paper>